<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8319] hbase-it tests are run when you ask to run all tests -- it should be that you have to ask explicitly to run them</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8319</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Up on trunk and on 0.95 apache builds, Sergey noticed that hbase-it tests are running.  Up to this, the convention was that you had to explicitly ask that they run but that changed somehow recently.  These tests are heavyweight, take a long time to complete, and are very likely to fail up on the apache infra (which is what we want of them but not as part of the general proofing build).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For now the tests have been artificially disabled up on builds.apache.org but their inclusion likely frustrates joe blow trying to do a local hbase packaging.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12641860">HBASE-8319</key>
            <summary>hbase-it tests are run when you ask to run all tests -- it should be that you have to ask explicitly to run them</summary>
